    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ENGINE COOLING SYSTEM - MAINTENANCE - ADJUST SHUTTER
        OPENING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ADJUST SHUTTER OPENING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Where shutters are used, adjust the shutter thermostat to open the shutters when the engine outlet
                    coolant is 10&#176;F. (5&#176;C.) above the engine thermostat opening temperature.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Example: For a 170&#176;F. (77&#176;C.) thermostat, the shutters should start to open when the engine
            outlet temperature is 180&#176;F. (82&#176;C.). The shutters should be fully open when the outlet coolant
            temperature reaches 190&#176;F. (88&#176;C.).
        </para>
    </svcproc>
